1) Clone the code from github
2) Copy .env.example file and and rename it in .env in root directory
3) Change database name in .env file
4) Apply "composer install" command in you terminal
5) Apply "php artisan migrate" command in your terminal

Please check postman collection in your root directory jsonCollection/Stripe.postman_collection

Create customer api
EndPoint : /api/create-customer
Method : POST
Parameter : name:test
            email:test@test.com
            password:12345678
            password_confirmation:12345678

List all customer api
EndPoint : /api/list-customer
Method : GET

Retrive customer api
EndPoint : /api/retrive-customer
Method : GET
Parameter : id:1

Update customer api
EndPoint : /api/update-customer
Method : POST
Parameter : id:1
            name:test01
            email:test01@test.com

You can test unit testing by using composer "test command"


